Here is the analysis for the KeyspaceOpsResources.list endpoint at /api/v0/ops/keyspace.

- Full HTTP request path

- Are all HTTP methods acceptable for this endpoint?
  - No. The root path /api/v0/ops/keyspace only has a GET handler defined. There are POST handlers on sub-paths (e.g., /cleanup, /refresh, /create, /alter), but not on the root path itself.

- HEAD
  - Not acceptable for this endpoint. There is no @HEAD method defined for the root path, only @GET.

- POST

- OPTIONS

- TRACE
  - Not acceptable for this endpoint. There is no @TRACE method defined.

- GET

- PUT
  - Not acceptable for this endpoint. No @PUT method is defined on the root path.

- DELETE
  - Not acceptable for this endpoint. No @DELETE method is defined on the root path.

- PATCH

Explanation:
- The class is annotated with @Path("/api/v0/ops/keyspace"), setting the base path for this resource.
- The root path (no additional @Path on the method) has a single HTTP method implemented: GET (the list endpoint).
- Other HTTP methods exist in this class but under sub-paths (e.g., /cleanup, /refresh, /create, /alter). They do not apply to the root path.
- There is no explicit HEAD/OPTIONS/TRACE/PUT/DELETE/PATCH method on the root path, so these are not supported for the base endpoint according to the code. The only supported method for /api/v0/ops/keyspace is GET.
